se in external tools like OpenClaw. This page explains:\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:652: Many extension channels are configured as `channels.<id>` and documented in their dedicated channel pages (for example Feishu, Matrix, LINE, Nostr, Zalo, Nextcloud Talk, Synology Chat, and Twitch).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration.md:78: Each channel has its own config section under `channels.<provider>`. See the dedicated channel page for setup steps:\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\doctor.md:161: - reminds you to enable remote debugging in the browser inspect page (for\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\index.md:10: Use this page for day-1 startup and day-2 operations of the Gateway service.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\local-models.md:14: If you want the lowest-friction local setup, start with [Ollama](/providers/ollama) and `openclaw onboard`. This page is the opinionated guide for higher-end local stacks and custom OpenAI-compatible local servers.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\openresponses-http-api.md:132: - PDFs are parsed for text. If little text is found, the first pages are rasterized\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\sandboxing.md:28: - noVNC observer access is password-protected by default; OpenClaw emits a short-lived token URL that serves a local bootstrap page and opens noVNC with password in URL fragment (not query/header logs).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:12: This page defines the strict contract enforced by `openclaw secrets apply`.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\troubleshooting.md:11: This page is the deep runbook.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\trusted-proxy-auth.md:13: > ?? **Security-sensitive feature.** This mode delegates authentication entirely to your reverse proxy. Misconfiguration can expose your Gateway to unauthorized access. Read this page carefully before enabling.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\security\\index.md:24: This page explains hardening **within that model**. It does not claim hostile multi-tenant isolation on one shared gateway.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\debugging.md:12: This page covers debugging helpers for streaming output, especially when a\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:416: This is usually a console code page mismatch on native Windows shells.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\troubleshooting.md:11: If you only have 2 minutes, use this page as a triage front door.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\ansible.md:15: The [openclaw-ansible](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw-ansible) repo is the source of truth for Ansible deployment. This page is a quick overview.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\docker-vm-runtime.md:75: The download URLs above are for x86_64 (amd64). For ARM-based VMs (e.g. Hetzner ARM, GCP Tau T2A), replace the download URLs with the appropriate ARM64 variants from each tool's release page.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\exe-dev.md:13: This page assumes exe.dev's default **exeuntu** image. If you picked a different distro, map packages accordingly.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\migrating-matrix.md:11: This page covers upgrades from the previous public `matrix` plugin to the current implementation.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\nix.md:15: The [nix-openclaw](https://github.com/openclaw/nix-openclaw) repo is the source of truth for Nix installation. This page is a quick overview.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\node.md:12: OpenClaw requires **Node 22.16 or newer**. **Node 24 is the default and recommended runtime** for installs, CI, and release workflows. Node 22 remains supported via the active LTS line. The [installer script](/install#alternative-install-methods) will detect and install Node automatically - this page is for when you want to set up Node yourself and make sure everything is wired up correctly (versions, PATH, global installs).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\raspberry-pi.md:149: **Service will not start** -- Check logs with `journalctl -u openclaw --no-pager -n 100` and run `openclaw doctor --non-interactive`.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\nodes\\troubleshooting.md:11: Use this page when a node is visible in status but node tools fail.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\platforms\\digitalocean.md:239: journalctl -u openclaw --no-pager -n 50\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\platforms\\raspberry-pi.md:361: journalctl -u openclaw --no-pager -n 100\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\platforms\\windows.md:137: systemctl --user status openclaw-gateway --no-pager\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\platforms\\mac\\canvas.md:32: If no `index.html` exists at the root, the app shows a **built-in scaffold page**.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\np